The paper deals with graph coloring, which is a fundamental topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The lower bound result relies on the Exponential Time Hypothesis (ETH), which is a well-established assumption in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The algorithmic techniques used in the paper involve graph algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), as well as combinatorial optimization and game theory (cs.GT). Finally, the paper also touches upon computational geometry, as it deals with the problem of coloring edges in a geometric graph (cs.CG).
